{"id":"7430","name":"bright-early-letter-of-the-law-edition-2","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Letter Of The Law Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2011-07-01T09:30:00-05:00","tags":["air quality alert","barnes &amp; noble","bath salts","borders","don&apos;t say gay","fourth of july","gannett","green parking program","heather byrd","jamie hollin","joe biddle","july 4th","layoffs","lebanon","mnps","obscene bumperstickers","radon","sky lanterns","TDOT","tennessean","tennessee state legislature","trucknutz","west end"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/x30mileswest/5861090419/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3137/5861090419_13409a57be.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"386\"></a></p><p>Good morning, Nashville, and happy July! <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/public-breastfeeding-among-150-new-state-laws-take-effect?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-LatestNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+Latest+News%29\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">July 1st is that magical day when all those new laws take effect that were debated and passed in this year&#x2019;s legislative session</a>. Among this year&#x2019;s laws are the removal of the one-year age limit on a child being breastfed in public, <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/story/15009792/stricter-offensive-bumper-sticker-law-takes-effect\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">a crackdown on obscene bumperstickers</a> (to our knowledge, TruckNutz&#x2122; are still okay), a sky lantern ban, ads on TDOT emergency trucks, and the removal of words like &#x201C;idiot,&#x201D; &#x201C;lunatic,&#x201D; and &#x201C;mentally retarded&#x201D; from Tennessee code, and that controversial teacher tenure change.</p><ul><li><strong>Free parking program starts today. </strong>Metro is also starting up the green parking program today. So if you drive <a href=\"http://nashvilleclerk.com/motor-vehicles/green-parking-permit/green-cars-list/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvilleclerk.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">one of these cars</a>, you can <a href=\"http://nashvilleclerk.com/wp-content/forms/motor_veh/green_form.pdf\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;download&apos;,&apos;nashvilleclerk.com/wp-content/forms/motor_veh/green_form.pdf&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">fill out this application form</a> and take it to one of the Davidson County Clerk&#x2019;s offices and pick up a $10 permit for free parking at <a href=\"http://www.nashvilledowntown.com/_files/docs/cbid_boundaries_2008-2017_terms.pdf\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;download&apos;,&apos;www.nashvilledowntown.com/_files/docs/cbid_boundaries_2008-2017_terms.pdf&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">all of these meters</a>. As for the rest of us, we can get our permits by donating to organizations that award carbon offset credits, though we&#x2019;d recommend checking with the Davidson County Clerk first to ensure the organization is eligible.</li><li><strong>Vanderbilt bookstore coming to West End. </strong>The gaping bookstore hole that Borders left at the corner of West End and 35th <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/article/20110630/NEWS01/110630006/2275/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">will soon be occupied by Vanderbilt&#x2019;s student bookstore</a>. Vandy is partnering with Barnes &amp; Noble to operate the bookstore which will sell books for the general public in addition to school books and merchandise.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; pieces.</strong> Metro Councilman Jamie Hollin wants to <a href=\"http://nashvillecitypaper.com/content/city-news/resolution-recognizes-students-who-protested-dont-say-gay-bill?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+NashvilleCityPaper-CityNews+%28Nashville+City+Paper+-+City+News%29\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">formally recognize the high school students who protested the &#x201C;Don&#x2019;t Say Gay&#x201D; bill</a> &#x2026; Lebanon&#x2019;s police chief is seeking to <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/story/15009086/lebanon-police-chief-wants-to-ban-bath-salts-incense\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">ban bath salts and incense</a> &#x2026; Following a News Channel 5 report, <a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/story/15008104/metro-vows-to-continue-testing-schools-for-radon\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Metro Schools officials are vowing to continue testing schools for dangerous radon levels</a> &#x2026; <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/story/15009426/air-quality-alert-issued-for-parts-of-mid-state\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">&#x2018;Tis the season for air quality alerts</a> &#x2026; It&#x2019;s going to be a <a href=\"http://nashvillewx.com/2011/07/few-high-clouds-this-morning-heat-builds-through-july-4th/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashvillewx.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">hot, hot July 4th</a> &#x2026; The <em>Tennessean</em> laid off more than a dozen newsroom employees yesterday <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/story/15010129/newspaper-lay-off-effects-long-time-sports-columnist\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">including longtime sports columnist Joe Biddle and entertainment writer Heather Byrd</a>.</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/x30mileswest/5861090419/in/pool-715021@N24/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Ryan Green</a></em>.</p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/06/23/bright-early-letter-of-the-law-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Letter Of The Law Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Letter Of The Law Edition</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/06/05/bright-early-cant-get-no-satisfaction-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Can&#x2019;t Get No Satisfaction Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Can&#x2019;t Get No Satisfaction Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}